Jay said:

> I found the little blue electrical connector to the... I think the cold idle jet, on the intake manifold was
loose and didn't have the wire clip to hold it on.  Could that be all it was?  Maybe a fuel delivery issue of
some kind???  It runs pretty well once it's started.

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------

The blue connector goes to the cold start valve. You really really need that cold start valve to be working on
a cold start. Hence the name 'cold start valve' :)

Sounds like that is all that is wrong.
